description: Beautiful and calm apartment in close vicinity of the Viktoria Park, Bergmannstrasse and the western centre of Berlin.
neighborhood_overview:
Description:
A stone's throw away you'll find the Viktoria-Park, for Berlin people known as the "Kreuzberg", with a lovely waterfall. An oasis of relaxation with a very nice and large children's playground next to a little Biergarten (Golgatha) and a high monument from where - weather permitting - you can enjoy a spectacular view over the city.

The Bergmannstraße with it's many cafés, bars, restaurants, second hand shops is just a couple of walking minutes away. There are wine dealers, supermarkets, pharmacies and one of the three last remaining historical market halls in Berlin. South of Bergmannstraße in the small side streets (Chamisso Platz) you'll think you've gone back to centuries past: Cobblestone streets and Wilhelminian style tenements with stucco decorations.

The closest supermarkets are Kaisers (corner Großbeerenstraße), ALDI, Lidl  and Getränke Hoffmann on the western end of Kreuzbergstraße. The Kaiser´s supermarket in Bergmannstraße is even open

Prenzlauer Berg is no doubt one of the most mythical districts of the city.
It embodies Berlin’s cultural heritage from diverse historical periods, proletarian and middle-class styles of the fin-de-siècle, just as the imprint of socialism.
What is more, there has always been a tradition of resistance and opposition giving birth to the spirit of creativity that incessantly surrounds you here.
The architecture should hold attention because in spite of the galloping renovation since the fall of the Wall, it still retains some of scars from the Second World War.

neighborhood_overview:
Neighbourhood and location:

The über-cool Prenzlauer Berg neighbourhood of Berlin is a hit with Berliner locals for its superb gastronomic offer and vintage shopping, Mauerpark's famed flea market, and brunch cafés. Countless restaurants, cafés and little shops create a unique atmosphere, unravelled in the rest of the city. 

Central,  yet quieter than Berlin Mitte, Prenzlauer Berg is also one of the prettiest neighbourhoods. Much of it escaped damage in the second world war and post-war redevelopment. 


Public Transportation:
Excellent public transport connections take you to Mitte in just a few minutes, where you can visit main Berlin attractions, such as Alexanderplatz, Museum Island or Hackescher Markt. Nearby S-Bahn: Prenzlauer Allee S9 , Ringbahn , S8; Nearby U-Bahn: Schönhauser Allee (U2). name: The Berlin Artist Apartment.
description:
A large art filled two bedroom holiday apartment sleeping up to four. In the heart of a famous Simon Dach street, in Berlin's hip Friedrichshain district, the apartment has many cafes, markets & bars just outside the front door. Situated close the leftovers of the wall, 02 stadium, and great public transport links - the perfect base to explore Berlin. The holiday apartment is officially registered, so there will be no last minute cancellations. 

2nd level (no lift), beautiful mansion block.
neighborhood_overview:
The Berlin Artist Apartment is situated in a pre-war apartment building in the heart Berlin's Friedrichshain district, east of Alexanderplatz. It is perhaps the last resort for Berlin's famous alternative subculture. The streets culture is colourful and vibrant: Left over artist squats merge with imposing monumental Stalin-era buildings. Late-nineteenth century apartment buildings, galleries, alternative bars, clubs and cafes permeate the streets. Simon Dach Strasse is a popular spot with students, artists, young families as well as young Berliners.

The front of the apartment building has a liquor and convenience shop, a fantastic bakery, café and icecream shop. Nearby Boxhagener platz hosts the fantastic farmers market on  Saturday, and the famous flea market on the Sunday. Reveler Str flea market is at the end of the Street.  There are a range of supermarkets nearby.

Many more cultural, sporting and shopping options are also within walking or cycling distance. A

My husband, Matthew Wild is a chef. Our son, Pablo Wild is nearly 15 and sees the world as his home. Our little one Hugo is loving the adventures. We travel the world a lot, probably over 100 countries now - we are big believers in world schooling - but when we are not nomadic, we live between Beautiful Port Douglas, Wonga Beach, Goa in India and Amazing Berlin. Come and stay in our charming homes oozing art, soul and creative vibes. Our homes are created with love, lots of hard work, and a passion of collecting and creating.  We search the world for items we love. As much as possible, we recycle building materials, and upcycle furniture. Our houses aren't fussy or pretentious, but they are all about charming you, inspiring you, and celebrating the creative spirit. We love to create homes that create beautiful conversations, and spaces that inspire warm heartedness, lots of laughter and precious memories. We hope we get to share our homes with you!

name: Quiet studio in Prenzlauer Berg near Mauerpark
description: Central and quiet apartment in period house in the heart of the Prenzlauer Berg. Perfect for couples and people who are looking for an authentic and relaxing Berlin experience in one of Berlin's most popular neighborhoods.
neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located in the beautiful and trendy Prenzlauer Berg district, known for its thriving café and art gallery culture.

In the Prenzlauer Berg you will find plenty of restaurants, kitsch boutiques and alternative-style bars. The popular Kollwitzplatz and Helmholzplatz are only a leisurely 10-20 min stroll away, same as the Kulturbrauerei, an old brewery with shops, nightlife and a free museum about life in the DDR. Not far from there are the Berlin wall walk and Berlin wall memorial.
 
If you are in Berlin on a Sunday, don't miss the nearby Mauerpark with its large flea market and renowned outdoor karaoke. A must see, especially on a sunny day!

Not too far from the apartment is “Volkspark Friedrichshain”. This large and popular park, with a fairytale fountain, film showings and beer gardens, is a nice place for hanging out in the summer. For those who prefer a more active holiday it offers  facilities for jogging, beach volleyball, bouldering
host_about:

We want to help make the world a better place and have comitted to donating a minimum of 10% of our profits.

description:
Our apt (90sqm / 1.000sqft) is in a 1893 historical building with 2 bedrooms (1 double, 1 triple), 2 bathrooms, fully-equipped kitchen and living room.

Centrally located in Prenzlauer Berg, Berlin's most beautiful area, in a quiet street with nice restaurants, cafés and lots of green!

Netflix is available on both TVs, as well as a fast internet connection (250Mb/s), washing machine and Nespresso machine with capsules selection.

We provide an iPhone 7 with internet, maps and guidebooks.
neighborhood_overview:
The area is one of the most trendy neighborhoods in Berlin, with lots of shops, bars and nice restaurants, all reachable by foot; we can provide you with list of the best places to eat and/or have a drink, please just ask (or check the guidebook in our profile).

The area is very quite and green, in a bicycle street (with priority to bikes) with a few cars passing by; it's also very safe (thanks to the two police stations in the area). In front of the house there is a church famous for having been the place where the peaceful revolution started (don't worry, the bell rings only during the day ;)

Mauerpark, also known as („wallpark” because of the Wall which passed through it) is just 20 minutes away, there you can relax or visit the famous flee market on Sunday.

In the area you can find several shops and supermarkets:
- mini-market next to our place, on the left
- Supermarket, postoffice and several shops in the Schönhauser Arkaden mall (5 minu
host_about:
We are a friendly couple who would be glad to rent our 90 sqm flat (about 960 sqft) to people traveling to Berlin :)
We are working for an internet startup and we would be more than happy to advise you about the best activities in the city and help you have a great time in one of the most vibrant capital cities of Europe.

name: Near KaDeWe & Kurfürstendamm
description: The 3 room apartment in Kalckreuthstraße 3 is an 80m² apartment with private bath and a comfortable kitchen located on the ground floor overlooking a quiet green courtyard garden.
neighborhood_overview: Die Kalckreuthstraße ist eine ruhige Anliegerstraße mit Bäumen und Antiquitätengeschäften. Sie liegt zwischen den U-Bahn-Stationen Wittenberg- und Nollendorfplatz. Man wohnt zwischen dem Kurfürstendamm und dem Potsdamer Platz, der Mitte West und der Mitte Ost in der Nähe des Tiergartens mit seinen Erholungsmöglichkeiten und dem Botschaftsviertel. Mittwochs und samstags ist auf dem nahe gelegenen Winterfeldtplatz ein über die Grenzen Berlins hinaus bekannter Markt. Die Berliner Innenstadt ist sehr weitläufig und deshalb zu Fuß nur teilweise erkundbar. Die Parksituation ist für Berliner Innenstadtverhältnisse recht entspannt.
host_about:

name: Private Wing in Penthouse - Bedroom Bath & Terrace
description:
A stunning way to visit Berlin. A private wing of our sunny Penthouse, with a big bedroom, terrace, large bathroom, separate entrance all to yourself.  Additionally you have shared access to our livingroom, open kitchen, two balconies, cathedral ceilings & skylight.

The livingroom and kitchen area are shared, while one bedroom, a large bathroom and a rear entrance are private to you.
neighborhood_overview:
This is the most socio-politically diverse neighborhood I have ever seen.  A place where you can literally sit down and talk with a sandalmaker, a surgeon, and an anarchist from three different countries over a burrito. 

It has restaurants, cafes, punk bars, undefined performance spaces, graffiti, squats, lounges, boutiques, skate shops, green parks, clubs, stalinist architecture, live music, and bookstores.
host_about: Avid Musician, Cyclist, Photographer, Fire Spinner, student of culture and rather professional Programmer.

name: Bright, Charming and Modern Altbau
description: The rare and much sought after Altbaus of Berlin are a joy to experience!  These are the grand apartments from before first world war with high ceilings and Flur that leads to each and every room. Come-in and enjoy this unique experience!  All-inclusive pricing, completely flexible cancellation and no check-in/out restrictions... we travel a lot and hence, we know what we expect when we are the guests! :) PS: Our nightly price is all-inclusive, no extra cleaning fees, no additional charges!
neighborhood_overview: This is the prime residential area of old West Berlin (American Sector).  Lush trees, clean and well maintained cobblestone roads and footpaths, beautiful apartment blocks splashed with gardens, parks, restaurants and pubs... Big Aldi is just 2 minutes walk away.
host_about:
Hi there!  I am Prasad and I live in three countries ... India, Germany and USA... I come from India and have job in USA and a home in Germany...over time, have made all three countries my home bases.  I love music, books, travel and capoeira!  I am married and have a lovely wife and two sons, 15 (ready to get his own car...yikes!!) and 6.  Our dog is Lucy - a loving, silly and energetic yellow Lab who turned 1 year old in April 2019...

As  guest, I like simple and clean accommodations that offer a unique perspective of the location.  Tips from the host on local restaurants, beaches, treks and shops make my day!

As host, I like guests that keep my apartment neat and clean. I also enjoy to get to know my guests and hear about their travels.  I try to offer all amenities and flexibility that I find useful as a guest while traveling.

In my travels and hosting adventures, I hope I am making this world a little bit better than before...

name: Ample parkside apartment Kreuzberg
description: Spacious, bright, artistically furnished apartment in the middle of the lively, colorful Kreuzberg, in a relaxed street with restaurants and sidewalk cafes. Right on the park, within walking distance to the banks of Spree and Landwehrkanal. Ideal for a relaxed and inspiring city holiday.
neighborhood_overview: The apartment, located at the Görlitzer Park, is quiet and yet in the midst of a lively and diverse neighborhood in Kreuzberg. In the house next door is a newsagent and bakery, 5 minutes walk through the park is a swimming pool with wave pool, 5 minutes walk to a children's animal farm, several playgrounds in the immediate area, 10 minutes walk to the charming bank of the Landwehr Canal, 15 minutes to the banks of the Spree, and many cafés, restaurants with affordable and delicious lunch and bars right in the street as well as in the surrounding neighborhood. There are small shops and supermarkets as well as two vegetable markets nearby, one specialized on organic food.

dancing tango Argentino, improvisation theater, action theater, contact improvisation, arts, especially performance art, firewalking, sustainability, Spanish language and culture, Buddhism, transformational learning, social entrepreneurship, social sculpuring, all around the process of innovation and creativity, meaningful conversations and good food.

name: Sunny Room in Beautiful Apartment in Kreuzberg
description: Welcome to my home, up high, away from the street, there's a wide view of the sunrise over Friedrichshain & Kreuzberg. I live with my lovely flat mate & singer song writer Cindo, and we will share a large kitchen, & a bathroom filled with plants.  My home is queer friendly and a safe, relaxing space for all people. Looking forward to sharing it with you.
neighborhood_overview:
Located in the heart of Kreuzberg right by the Spree, we are very happy to be living in one of the most tolerant and versatile areas in the world.

Food:
*********
Eisenbahnstrasse is home to the popular 'Street Food Thursdays' in 'Martkhalle 9', with special programs almost every weekend. Friday's there's also an outdoor market on Lausitzer Platz (4min by foot). 

Within 5min walking distance we have some of the best restaurants in the city, both very affordable and a bit more expensive. We are happy to help you find what you like.  We possibly have the best middle eastern street food in europe all within a 10 min walk. Also excellent Italian, Indian, Vietnamese, & Burger Joints all over our neighborhood. Supermarkets Netto, Lidl & Aldi are open late and are all 5 minutes away.

neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the City Center West (where the district of Charlottenburg borders with Wilmersdorf)  - just a few steps off the famous "Kurfürstendamm" boulevard, where you will find a wealth of international restaurants and designer stores, as well as bakeries and supermarkets (some of them are open 'til midnight and some are open 24/7) 
To visit the world-renowned SCHAUBÜHNE theater - you simply cross the street.

This safe neighborhood in the City Center West is so sought after that even the former mayor of Berlin has chosen to live here !
host_about:
After having worked in New York City for decades,we retired and moved to the vibrant city of Berlin. The cozy studio apartment we are offering used to be our own vacation home while we were living in NYC.
In our free time we love to take advantage of Berlin's extensive offerings of cultural life - museums, theaters, concerts etc. We also love to ride our bikes to explore the city and its surrounding forests and many lakes.  If you like, we can give you a tour through the very dynamic city of Berlin - on foot, on bike or using its excellent public transportation system.
We would also be interested in exchanging/switching apartments with other airbnb hosts in our favorite travel spots NYC and Barcelona-Sitges or Gran Canaria.
Please, feel free to contact us if you would like to know more about us and the apartment.

description: A well-situated furnished shared apartment in Charlottenburg, located in west Berlin, 5 mins. walk to UB Richard Wagner Platz, Bus M45 to any destination in the city or outskirts. Guests who look for party atmosphere, please look elsewhere, this is mainly residential area.
neighborhood_overview:
Charlottenburg has a very famous castle which is a few mins. walk.
Museum Bergruen, Heimat Museum, Rathaus Charlottenburg, Charlottenburg Pottery are within walking distances.
Stadtbibliothek near the Rathaus and underground station offers free wifi access from 11am to 7pm.
All the other sightseeing places are easily reached by underground station U-7 Richard Wagner Platz, or Bus M45 which goes to Zoologischer Garten, Technical University, etc.
BER airport to S-Bahn Charlottenburg is frequent, check the local transportation app.
Everything is very convenient, there is even a supermarket downstairs.

My best cooking recipes have been taught by the locals and the best sightseeing trips organized by the host families.
I am looking forward to meet you and wish you a great stay in Berlin!

Steglitzer Schlossstraße, one of the largest and most modern shopping streets in Berlin is about 1.5 km away. Nearby: Summer outdoor pool and Berlin Planetarium at the Insulaner. The southern area, a former marshalling yard, which was "forgotten" until the 80s. Old signal boxes, rails leading to nowhere, locomotives, weathered engine sheds and a water tower have been reclaimed and overgrown by nature. In between, artists have (exhibited) their works, a total work of art that is unique in Europe. Those who climb the 78m high disused gasometer behind Südbahnhof are rewarded with a breathtaking view over Berlin. Other Schöneberg highlights: The lively Winterfeldmarkt, which takes place every Wednesday and Saturday. The KaDeWe department store on Wittenbergplatz with a gourmet floor. Akazienstrasse and Goltzstrasse: lots of small stores with delicatessen, fashion, accessories, junk, antiques, cafés and restaurants.

neighborhood_overview:
Friedrichshain. Next to the districts of Prenzlauer Berg and Kreuzberg.

Rough here, lively there, then relaxed and almost idyllic, colorful and urban - Friedrichshain, its charm comes from these contrasts, from this plurality.

In the north - the Volkspark Friedrichshain is particularly popular with young families. West is characterized by the Stalin buildings on Karl-Marx-Allee and prefabricated buildings. East - mainly by old buildings. The border is the axis Warschauer Straße-Petersburger Straße. Preferred part of party people and tourists is around the Warsaw Bridge, RAW site and Simon-Dach-Strasse. Synonyms for night and cultural life.

Things get quiet again towards Boxhagener Platz. Lawn for sunbathing, a large playground and fountain, which is used by children to splash about in summer. At the weekend there is a market/flea market all around.

name: Great value studio in Prenzlauer Berg. StayBearlin
description:
Centrally located studio perfect for couples and people who are looking for an authentic Berlin experience in one of Berlin's most popular neighborhoods.
Free public parking is available about 500 meters away from the apartment. The train and tram station and two supermarkets are only 200m away.
neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located in a residential area of the beautiful and trendy Prenzlauer Berg district, known for its thriving café and art gallery culture.

In the Prenzlauer Berg you will find plenty of restaurants, kitsch boutiques and alternative-style bars. The popular Kollwitzplatz and Helmholzplatz are a leisurely 20-25 min stroll away, same as the Kulturbrauerei, an old brewery with shops, nightlife and a free museum about life in the DDR. Not far from there are the Berlin wall walk and Berlin wall memorial.
 
If you are in Berlin on a Sunday, don't miss the nearby Mauerpark with its large flea market and renowned outdoor karaoke. A must see, especially on a sunny day!

Not too far from the apartment is “Volkspark Friedrichshain”. This large and popular park, with a fairytale fountain, film showings and beer gardens, is a nice place for hanging out in the summer. For those who prefer a more active holiday it offers  facilities for jogging, beach volle
host_about:
We are an Irish-Polish/German couple. 
We moved to Berlin about 13 years ago and are looking forward to sharing our favourite Berlin spots with you.

We have prepared an extensive guide book for all our guests with many tips on what to do in Berlin, where to eat and where to go out. It also has a section for parents, winter, summer.

We want to help make the world a better place and have comitted to donating a minimum of 10% of our profits.

name: nettes Einzelzimmer 1.3 (1. Etage)
description:
The house is located in the historic working-class district Böhmisch-Rixdorf with numerous cafes, shopping, leisure opportunities in the vicinity.
We are part of the movement “Give Anti-Communism No Chance!”, initiated in 2020 by the “Internationalist Alliance against Right-wing Development, Fascism and War”.  
Offer: knowledgeable city walks on relevant topics, also to the surrounding area or tourist highlights. Groups up to 8 people 20 euros, each additional person 2 euros.
neighborhood_overview:
Die Unterkünfte liegen im Bezirk Neukölln mitten im 1737 gegründeten historischen Arbeiterviertel Böhmisch-Rixdorf. In unmittelbarer Umgebung: Cafés, Bars, Einkaufsmöglichkeiten, Neuköllner Oper, Kinos, zahlreiche Galerien, Volkspark Hasenheide und Tempelhofer Feld. 
In Berlin bieten sich zahlreiche Möglichkeiten, historische und moderne Kultur besuchen, sich zu erholen, das Zusammenwachsen von Ost und West intensiv und lebendig erleben. Besondere Anziehungspunkten sind der historische Stadtkern mit dem Brandenburger Tor und der Straße unter den Linden sowie dem angrenzenden Regierungsviertel, einzigartige Museen, eine traditionsreiche Industriekultur, moderne Architektur oder die städtischen Naherholungsgebiete.
Auf Wunsch gestalten wir Stadtführungen mit sachkundigen Stadtführern. Hierzu beraten wir Sie gern. Für Gruppen bis  8 Personen bieten wir Führungen für 20 Euro an, jede weitere Person 2 Euro. Die Nutzung des Berliner Nahverkehrs kostet extra.

Herzlich willkommen in meiner Unterkunft in Berlin Neukölln

Ich würde mich freuen, wenn Ihr Euch für meine Wohnung entscheidet und stehe Euch gerne mit Tipps zur Seite.

A highlight here is a stand specialising in a finer version of the renowned Berliner Currywurst. On Thursdays, the Kollwitzplatz organic market offers a smaller selection, which nevertheless covers all your needs. The well-known flea market, open on Sundays, at the Mauer Park is also walking distance.

We love to travel for work and to visit friends elsewhere on this earth. Suraya has been on the move since she was six months. 

It has been wonderful meeting people from around the world. We are good at figuring out how much privacy or support our guests wish for.

description: In a prime location, immerse yourself in a lively Berlin with its typical flair and enjoy a stylish temporary home right on the Spree in the heart of vibrant Kreuzberg. Set in a former jam factory, this quiet apartment was decorated in January 2012 with love and a sense of security for beautiful interiors. Relaxed beach bars, trendy clubs and good restaurants are just around the corner.  Countless real Berlin pubs are open all night and for the appetite in between there are snack stalls with kebab, pizza and homemade burgers of first quality. It is five minutes to the Künstlerhaus Bethany, ten minutes to the "Badeschiff", a swimming pool with a pontoon floating on the Spree, from where you can admire large passing ships. Quickly get there and away The transport connection is perfect. You have 300 m to the U-Bahn (subway), 800 m to the S-Bahn (subway) and can reach all the cultural highlights and centres of Berlin in no time.  Your home away from home The apartment has been equipped wit
neighborhood_overview:
Ein italienisches und ein türkisches Café befindet sich gleich gegenüber. Dort gibt es Kaffee sowie Mittagsgerichte und Kuchen. Ein Supermarkt ist 3 Minuten entfernt. Am Schlesischen Tor gibt es einen großen Bio-Supermarkt. Hier im Haus gibt es einen Kiosk (Späti) der 24 Stunden am Tag geöffnet hat. Perfekt für ein Feierabendgetränk.
Es gibt unzählige kleine Restaurants, Bars und Cafes, wenige Gehminuten entfernt.
Kreuzberg ist ein weitläufiger Stadtteil, in dem viele Studenten und Künstler wohnen. Hier findet man auch Secondhandläden, Street-Art, zwanglose Bars und Imbissstände.
host_about:

Ich wohne gleich nebenan und stehe Euch gerne mit Tipps zur Seite. 
Wir freuen uns über nette Gäste, die unser Leben mit neuen Anregungen bereichern!

Berlin as a microcosm: lively, colorful and multicultural - this is the area between the Landwehr Canal and the Hasenheide called Graefe-Kiez. Here you will find about 100 attractive shops for good shopping possibilities and the gastronomic offer of cafes, bars and restaurants is extremely divers. Those who prefer to relax alone or with your partner on a longish walk can do this extensively on the banks of the Landwehr Canal, which provides on both sides long hiking trails. This route is also popular among joggers. The public park Hasenheide in turn provides an open-air cinema, a small zoo for children and large areas for relaxation. The former Tempelhof Airport, now called Tempelhofer Freiheit, is Berlin´s largest park area and within walking distance from the apartment.

name: Spend the night in the oldest house in Berlin!
description: Here you will be sleeping in the oldest residential building in Berlin from the 17th century, the only worldly building left from the extension of the medieval town, with original architecture on its original site - even if you would hardly notice it ...
neighborhood_overview:
You really will live in the oldest residential building in Berlin - even if you would hardly know it, since a Mediterranean style outer facade was added during renovation in the nineties and even native Berliners and walkers pass it unwittingly every day. So do not be surprised if a group with an experienced city guide stops to look up at the house. You are in a 100% listed building. 
 
A 17th century building "lives" and "moves" - so you are not afraid of creaking floorboards or the like - it is certainly not the ghosts of old times ... adjoining street noise, tourists or sometimes a night-time act on the street or a passing police car, let you know despite well-insulated windows, that you are still in the Berlin of the 21st century.  
 
As well as part of the city wall, the oldest dwelling-house and the oldest restaurant, Waisenstrasse also has Berlin's oldest cemetery - the Parochialfriedhof - as well as the ruins of the old Franciscan monastery. All other sights

The arcitecture of the houses around are very beautiful and in the old Berlin style.
Just stepping out the door a minute away you find a selection of nice very good restaurants from italian, german, spanish, indian, asian, japanese  and many others. 
A small supermarket is only 30 seconds away where you find everything for a good start. 
Opposite is a bakery, coffeeshop & healthfoodstore. 
Charming small boutiques and Cafes are everywhere
The S-Bahn station Charlottenburg with buses and taxi are only 3 minutes away. It takes you only minutes to the center of Berlin. 

The famous Kurfürstendamm is only a few minutes away. 
The big shopping mal Wilmersdorfer Arcaden also only minutes away. 
The Aspria Fitnessclub & Spa offers excellent fitness programs and Spa treatments.

neighborhood_overview:
Tempelhof is a primarily residential district in central South-West Berlin, bordering Schöneberg in the West, Kreuzberg in the North and Neukölln in the East. Traditionally a well-maintained middle-class neighbourhood,
it has recently gained in attention due to the conversion of Tempelhof Airport into a huge park. Still being spared from local hypes, it offers a great mixture of comfort and proximity to all major destinations. It is a place that makes you feel at home, yet to be overcrowded by tourists.

- great infrastructure (5 supermarkets, shopping arcade and shopping street 5-10 min. walking distance, underground station 10 min. walking distance, IKEA few min. by car or 15 min. by bus, city highway and S-Bahn closeby, several busses etc.)
- 10 min walk from the quaint and historical tempelhof harbour populated with cafes and restaurants
- restaurants of all major cuisines (Indian, Chinese, Greek, Turkish, Thai, Italian, German) within walking distance<br /

name: Gästeappartement in Rudow (App. 2)
neighborhood_overview:
Rudow ist der südlichste Ortsteil von Neukölln und liegt fast an der Stadtgrenze. Im Ortskern mit Einkaufsstrasse endet die U-Bahn-Linie 7, die längste U-Bahn-Linie der Stadt, der Flughafen Schönefeld liegt von hier nur wenige Busminuten entfernt. Viele Einfamilien- und Reihenhäuser prägen das Ortsbild. Wer hier wohnt, schätzt die stadtnahe und ruhige Lage.
Im romantischen Altstadtkern findet man alles für den täglichen Bedarf, Friseur, Supermärkte, Fleischer, Bäcker, Blumengeschäfte, Bioladen, Schuster, Optiker, Ärzte, Apotheken.
Rudow zeichnet sich durch seine gute Infrastruktur und die zahlreichen weitläufigen Park- und Grünanlagen mit hohem Freizeitwert aus.
Ein großes Angebot an Kinderbetreuung und Schulen sowie zahlreichen Ärzten und Sportvereine in direkter Umgebung machen den Stadtteil zu einer beliebten Wohngegend. Rudow-ein Ort mit Lebensqualität

name: Stylish Urban Retreat in a Beautiful Neighborhood
description: Experience our artist-owned space, where work, comfort and ecological living seamlessly blend together. Book your stay and enjoy the beauty,  and tranquility of this apartment.
neighborhood_overview: Prenzlauer Berg, also known as "Prenzlberg," has undergone a remarkable transformation since the reunification, evolving from a trendy district to an affluent family-friendly neighborhood, making it one of the most sought-after areas in Berlin. It has attracted a diverse mix of young professionals, families, and artists. The facades of the historic buildings have been painted in vibrant colors, giving the district and the city a fresh new look. Today, you'll find a plethora of high-quality shops and organic markets, such as the one at Kollwitzplatz, featuring local producers from Berlin and Brandenburg. The area is rich in bustling shopping streets, including Hufelandstraße, known for its artistic and deco shops, charming vintage boutiques, delightful vegan restaurants, and the scenic Volkspark Friedrichshain with its beautiful terraces.
host_about: Hello, I'm choreographer and, together  with my wife Altea, who is from Costa Rica, we run our own Dance and Yoga Studio in Berlin, Prenzlauer Berg called Caramba tanz&co (Just (Hidden by Airbnb) Caramba and tanz). We've got three lovely girls, the eldest has already left home and is studying abroad. I love to cook and, having worked in France many times, I appreciate the magic  of fresh ingredients and try very hard not to ruin them. Living and working abroad is an important part of my life. I have seen many hotels and grew to like the personal touch of a private home instead, so I think airbnb is a great idea! When I am in Berlin, I love to take trips to the lakes and to our garden in Potsdam or I just enjoy sitting in my favorite café, reading the newspaper and having a chat with friends passing by. Prenzlauer Berg is a bit of a village within the city of Berlin, you quickly get to know each other and you'll soon find your own favorite spots. Berlin is a very exciting place to be right now, things are still on the move, great artists, new architecture and lots of room for improvement and for your own ideas!

neighborhood_overview: Neukoelln, a traditionally rough-around-the-edges working class district, has undergone a radical transformation in the last decade, and now counts among Berlin's  most characteristic and sought-after districts.  A young, cosmopolitan crowd of international students, artists and hipsters now roams its streets, crowding up the numerous art galleries, typical Berlin bars and international eateries, side by side with the local - predominantly Turkish - population that settled here in the 60s and 70s. This multitude of cultures and subcultures mingle while still maintaining their identities and insofar arguably make Neukoelln - especially in its northern and most central part where this flat is located - the most authentic expression of Berlin's postmodern character. Literally across the street from the flat, you'll find a supermarket. Within a 5 minutes' walk from the flat, you´ll find shopping malls, the parks Hasenheide and Tempelhofer - the former airport turned into a one-of-a-kind, o

I'm also a traveler myself: one who deeply values the flat-sharing experience, as a guest as much as a host, for the personal connections that come into being. name: My home in Berlin might be yours !
description:
!!! COVID PRECAUTIONS: the apartment is cleaned after each visit according to the process recommended by Airbnb and the medical authorities !!!

Hello, I am Yves, french guy living in Paris and Berlin and I rent my berliner flat when I'm not there : located in the heart of Friedrichshain, the apartment is quiet, bright, central, ideally connected to the most central areas of town.
It will be all yours when I am away from Germany. I hope you’ll love it as much as I do.
neighborhood_overview: See Travelers ressources
host_about:
I made my first trip to Berlin in dec. 1988, just one year before the wall fell down. I started to go there more regularly 10 years ago and it soon became obvious that I needed my own place there : stressless life, friendly and open minded people, solidarity and kindness in every behavior, I found there exactly what I needed after 17 years living in Paris (…).

I bought my apartment end of february 2012 and started to renew it all by myself. It is not yet fully decorated, but already comfortable and I’m proud of what I made of it. If you come several times, you will notice the changes all through the years.

I any case, I’ve tried to make it the more comfortable I can, for myself, but also for my guest, so that we can all have a real home while discovering Berlin.

Hope to hear from you soon.
Yves

name: private Bedroom with en suite bath near Südstern
description: Our flat is quiet, yet near bustling neighborhoods. One block away is Körtestrasse with cafes, restaurants, grocery stores and other locally owned businesses. A short walk from the Landwehrkanal and Gräfekiez in one direction and Bergmannstrasse in the other, it is in the heart of Kreuzberg, yet tucked away from the busier neighborhoods.  Public transport is excellent: one block from the U7 Südstern station and two from the M41 bus, so it is very easy to get to the central station and airport.
neighborhood_overview:
Südstern is a beautiful place to stay. Our street is lovely, there are plenty of parks and playgrounds nearby. Körtestrasse is our local shopping street, with small independent shops that have almost everything one needs (wine shop, supermarket with great produce, bookstore, cafes, restaurants, pharmacy, etc). On Saturdays there is a lovely market at the end of the street that is worth a visit. And two of the best bakeries in the city are within a 5 minute walk. 

We are close to the canal, and near a number of other neighborhoods with shops, cafes, restaurants, record stores etc.  The U7 subway makes it easy to get to the airport, and the M41 Bus makes it easy to get to the central train station. 

There aren't so many hotels and Airbnbs in this part of Kreuzberg, which means it is not quite as touristy as other areas of the city. Yet you are very quickly in historic Mitte and are not far away from Berlin's famous nightlife spots. It is a great base for seeing the

The Kulturforum at Potsdamer Platz includes several state museums and the Berlin Philharmonic. The new National Gallery, Cultural Forum, Philharmonic Hall, State Library and Potsdamer Platz can be reached on foot in 5 - 10 minutes. You can reach the Tiergarten, one of the largest and most beautiful parks in Berlin, by bike in no more than 5 minutes. Another park is the Park am Gleisdreieck, which offers beach volleyball fields, a skate park, playgrounds and natural gardens. Culture and subculture are closely related in this area. Shrill bars like the Kumpelnest 3000 and hip fashion designers in the building complex of the former TAGESSPIEGEL publishing house shake hands. The Winter Garden on the other hand inspires visitors with constantly changing shows. Right next to it, in a beautifully restored old Berlin building with fantastically designed courtyard

description:

neighborhood_overview:
Kreuzberg is the place to be! Live amongst original Berliners, artists, families, students and foreigners alike with stylish clubs and cool underground bars just nearby. Nowhere else in Berlin is it as colourful!

Dozens of original restaurants and clubs, supermarkets, bike rentals, delicious bakeries and cozy coffee shops are just a few steps away.
host_about:
Meine Frau Julia und ich sind in Brandenburg groß geworden und Anfang der 2000er-Jahre nach Berlin gezogen. 

Die Leidenschaft, Gastlichkeit und Hingabe, die wir während unserer Reisen durch die ganze Welt erfahren durften, haben uns inspiriert, selbst Gastgeber zu werden. Zuerst in Berlin, unserer neuen Heimat. Und als die Geburt unserer Kinder den Blick aufs Leben änderte, die Reisen in die Ferne weniger wurden, da lernten wir Brandenburg neu kennen.

Wir haben viel darüber gelernt, was Urlaub mit Kindern bedeutet und dass es oft die kleinen Dinge sind, die den Unterschied zwischen Urlaubsstress und echter Erholung ausmachen.

Warm heatings, Oak floor, Original Vintage-DDR style, 6 suspension points for Shibari, Yoga Matts, decorated with original art works, Wifi, Dishwasher, Coffee Mokas!  
ABSOLUTELY NO PARTY, NO EVENTS, & NO LOUD MUSIC !
Please DO NOT BOOK it for Photo/Video shoots, Contact me and a different deal must be agreed
neighborhood_overview:
Friedrichshain-Kreuzberg, the heart of night life in Berlin. The flat is located at walkable distance from famous night clubs as Berghain, Watergate, Katerblau. 
Also Mercedes Arena and Universal Studios are at 5 minutes walk.
The East side Gallery with its famous murales are around the corner,
as well as the famous RAW area of revaler strasse. 
However the area is also quiet with restaurants and bio markets nearby.
Boxi flea market on sunday is a not to be missed for the lovers of vintage and antiquites that dont want to suffer in the overcrowed mauer park
(still nice and reachable with 15 minutes of m10 tram).
host_about:
I live in a huge old flat (100% original berliner altbau) and travel a lot for work and holidays.
When I travel you have the chance to rent the all flat for yourself, when I am  here I love to host and meet new people from all over the world.

I am a photographer and a tango dancer. I am very open minded, I have been living and working in Rome, London, Paris, New York.
My girlfriend often helps me in the flat.
We are very calm and quiet and silent, and I like that atmosphere in the flat.
Please only book these rooms if you are able to enter and respect someone's else home and being able to interact with strangers.
Those who are looking only for a cheap accommodation during their crazy weekends in Berlin, please go to a youth hostel.

name: Nice Apartment with Parkview*15min to PotsdamerPl
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the green south-west of Berlin in the district of Lichterfelde Ost, the oldest residential area of the capital. The apartment is surrounded by imaginatively designed historic villas, parks and avenues. The residential area combines in a unique way liveliness, green and urban diversity. Lichterfelde offers everything for a comfortable stay within walking distance: From small parks numerous shopping, weekly market and organic stores, to coffee roasting and delicatessen. In the many international bars and restaurants can be found from breakfast to dinner numerous food delights to suit every budget. 
At the same time you can reach by bus and S-Bahn Berlin's main attractions in a short time.

host_about:
Me reinstalo en la Ciudad de México, después de haber vivido 20 años en algunos países en el exterior  y me reencuentro con mi maravilloso y mágico país.  Dejé de ser turista y me convertí en viajera.  Me gusta ir a un solo lugar y quedarme un mínimo de dos semanas.   
Retorné a mi viejo barrio colonial de Coyoacán en esta ciudad, pero continuo añorando, sobre todo, mi estancia de 5 años en Alemania. 

Por esa agradable experiencia en este último país, dejé un studio, recién renovado en Berlín, última ciudad en la que viví y cuando no lo uso, lo rento.  Cuando estoy en Berlín rento mi departamento en Coyoacán, DF México. 
(El de Berlín me lo administra la Sra. Kaschubat a quien pueden contactar en m.kaschubat@fls-international.de  . Yo proporcionaré mas datos en el momento que se confirme con Airbnb alguna reservación. Me encantaría hacerlo yo misma pero lamentablemente no me es posible.   La administradora, mi amiga, es encantadora, formal, eficiente y muy entusiasta.  Siempre abierta a sugerencias y a aceptar la crítica constructiva, que ella aprovecha, para hacer constantes mejoras o modificaciones).
El departamento en Coyoacán lo administro yo directamente, pues es donde paso la mayor parte de mi tiempo.

In it dozens of different nationalities come together and learn to live side by side with their differences and similarities. To wander around this area is quite an experience. With its typical shops and markets it is another one of the peculiar city areas, both for the ambiance and for the beautiful 19th century architecture of the buildings.
The Blücher Boardinghouse is specifically located in a privileged area of this Berlin district. Its surroundings house, specially at Bergmannstrasse, Graefestrasse and Dieffenbachstrasse a number of shops, restaurants, cafes, and bars where you can go out for a drink at night.
Just steps away from the green area of the Landwerkkanal, you can enjoy the beautiful architecture of the buildings while talking a walk along the banks.

neighborhood_overview:
Prenzlauer Berg is no doubt one of the most mythical districts of the city.
It embodies Berlin’s cultural heritage from diverse historical periods, proletarian and middle-class styles of the fin-de-siècle, just as the imprint of socialism.
What is more, there has always been a tradition of resistance and opposition giving birth to the spirit of creativity that incessantly surrounds you here.
The architecture should hold attention because in spite of the galloping renovation since the fall of the Wall, it still retains some of scars from the Second World War.

name: Tauts Home - Hufeisensiedlung Berlin
description: Located in the UNESCO World Heritage Hufeisensiedlung (Horseshoe Estate) by famous architect Bruno Taut. Rentable house of the 1920s with garden for design lovers: restored true to the original, frequently awarded and mentioned in press and media.
neighborhood_overview:
Only a few hundred meters from Taut’s Home and the famous Horseshoe Estate stands Schloss Britz, a handsome classicist building in leafy surrounds with a manor and farm converted for cultural events. In the one-time stables you’ll now find two recommendable fine restaurants and two museums. What is more, is that the hip districts of Neukölln and Kreuzberg are just a few subway stations away. To go to the Centre (i.e. to Bahnhof Friedrichstraße or Alexanderplatz) takes about 20-25 minutes. For more info please see:
www.tautshome.com/umgebung (about the environs)
host_about:
TAUTES HEIM ist ein Projekt von Liebhabern für Liebhaber: Katrin und ich sind privat und beruflich stark im Bereich Architektur und Denkmalschutz engagiert und wurde für Tautes Heim mehrfach ausgezeichnet. Wir haben bei Renovierung und Ausstattung unseres Kleinods selbst viel Hand angelegt und hoffen durch die Vermietung diese Arbeit irgendwann refinanzieren zu können. Wir wohnen einige Straßen weiter und kennen uns vor Ort hervorragend, aber auch vielen anderen interessanten Ecken Berlins ganz gut aus. Wenn Du/Sie/ihr im Tauten Heim zu Gast sein wollt – Wir freuen uns immer, interessante Menschen oder auch neue Orte kennen zu lernen ...

Taut‘s Home is a place specially designed for architecture lovers. This is our personal and professional passion, too. And it was our motivation for creating this very unique place that has been frequently awarded. The rent helps us to refund our expenses for something that comes quite close to a type of museum that was still missing in Berlin. Katrin and I are living just a few blocks away and have very good knowledge about the estates history and a bunch of other places worth seeing in Berlin. We would be glad to have you as our guests and are always eager to meet new interesting people or discover special places ourselves ...

description: Great flat, stylish and cozy at the same time, in THE ´place-to-be-neighborhood´ with a breathtaking view over the city. Enjoy!
neighborhood_overview:
Once enclosed on three sides by the Berlin Wall, this former West Berlin neighbourhood, immediately south of the river Spree, drew immigrants, hippies, artists and squatters while the city was divided. It feels more gentrified and upscale these days but still has a revolutionary 
streak. 
More than anything it is the atmosphere that makes Kreuzberg so unique. There are no other parts of the city where there is so much going on. If you come, rent a bike: it's by far the best way to get around.

"Kreuzberg is also renowned for having quirky cafes offering some of the cities finest coffee and cake.
Summer days draw the crowds to Kreuzbergs famous GÖRLITZER PARK - a lush and spacious chill-out place popular for BBQ's and outdoor performances. Much more than just vast expanses of green grass and trees, the park also houses a petting zoo, several sports fields and playgrounds, a lake...oh, and a glow-in-the-dark mini-golf course!  
The park now often plays host

Ich reise gern und hierbei faszinieren mich besonders die asiatischen und afrikanischen Länder. Lesen macht mir Spaß und hierbei fesselt mich ein guter Krimi genauso wie Sachbücher über politische Themen, ausländische Kulturen und Menschen. Im Fernsehen schaue ich mir am liebsten Dokumentationen über fremde Länder und Kulturen an. Aber auch ein guter Spielfilm bereitet mir Vergnügen. 
Mir ist es wichtig, dass meine Gäste sich wie zu Hause fühlen. Wenn es Probleme gibt oder irgendwas fehlt - ein Anruf genügt. In meiner Abwesenheit kümmert sich mein Mann Michael um alles. 
Ich selbst habe bereits mehrfach über Airbnb gebucht und ich finde, es ist eine einmalige Gelegenheit, Land und Leute kennen zu lernen. Kein Hotel dieser Welt bietet solch eine Gelegenheit. 
Herzlichst Silvia 
ENGLISH
I was born in Germany and I'm living in Berlin for about 40 years now. I am married and have two children. As a journalist, I worked for various TV channels, e.g. RIAS TV, Deutsche Welle TV, n-tv news-channel. Now I'm working as a press officer for an international charityorganization. I love traveling and I'm fascinated particularly from Asian and African countries and their people. Reading a book is fun and I'm either fascinated by a good thriller as well as non-fiction books on political issues, foreign cultures and people. On television I mostly watch documentaries about foreign countries and cultures. But a good movie enjoys me as well.
I find it important that my guests feel at home. If there are problems or something is missing - just call. In my absence, my husband Michael takes care of everything. I also booked accommodations via airbnb and it is a fantastic possibility to get in good contact with people and their town. No hotel can offer this possibility.
Warm regards and you are very welcome. Silvia

name: Charming studio in Prenzlauer Berg by StayBearlin
description:
Centrally located studio perfect for couples and people who are looking for an authentic Berlin experience in one of Berlin's most popular neighborhoods.
Free public parking is available 500 meters away from the apartment. The train and tram station and two supermarkets are only 200m away.
neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located in a residential area of the beautiful and trendy Prenzlauer Berg district, known for its thriving café and art gallery culture.

In the Prenzlauer Berg you will find plenty of restaurants, kitsch boutiques and alternative-style bars. The popular Kollwitzplatz and Helmholzplatz are a leisurely 20-25 min stroll away, same as the Kulturbrauerei, an old brewery with shops, nightlife and a free museum about life in the DDR. Not far from there are the Berlin wall walk and Berlin wall memorial.
 
If you are in Berlin on a Sunday, don't miss the nearby Mauerpark with its large flea market and renowned outdoor karaoke. A must see, especially on a sunny day!

Not too far from the apartment is “Volkspark Friedrichshain”. This large and popular park, with a fairytale fountain, film showings and beer gardens, is a nice place for hanging out in the summer. For those who prefer a more active holiday it offers  facilities for jogging, beach volle
host_about:
We are an Irish-Polish/German couple. 
We moved to Berlin about 13 years ago and are looking forward to sharing our favourite Berlin spots with you.

We have prepared an extensive guide book for all our guests with many tips on what to do in Berlin, where to eat and where to go out. It also has a section for parents, winter, summer.

We want to help make the world a better place and have comitted to donating a minimum of 10% of our profits.

name: art-space loft with terrace. bikes!
description:
If you want to live in an amazing location, where you are practically in the sky, 
all above the roofs of Berlin, seeing the most beautiful sunsets of the city...
the art- loft is your location. 
It's no simulation of a hotel room or a bourgeois flat, but an art loft with a bohemian touch, with lots of space and light (from many windows and 3 light domes on the ceilings) with an unbeatable view, where you can enjoy the most beautiful sunsets in Berlin. Tempelhofer Park  just around the corner!
neighborhood_overview:
And nearly the most exiting fact: the flat is just 2 walking minutes from 2 big parks: one is the park Hasenheide, with lots of trees and lawn, and the other is the former airport Tempelhof, now transformed to an original park, in which you may rollerblade or bicycle on the slopes, that ones where used by airplanes. Or one can just hang around on the enormous lawn or have a grill party!
since the neighborhood (Kruezkölln) has become very trendy and lots of artists and young people are living there.
Still my flat is in a very calm location.
In the same house is a bicycle-shop, wish provides you good bikes for only 4 Euros a day. You have to say my name ( Nina) and you will get them without showing or leaving any documents.
host_about: i am a dancer and visual artist, teaching also sometimes in switzerland mathematics and languages. this seems to be a big contrast but i like to switch from one mental or physical theme to another...

name: Bright Top Floor Flat with Terrace
host_about:
Hi there,

Allow me to introduce myself: André, 26, Friedrichshainer.
I've been living in this wonderful neighborhood since nearly four years and I don't wanna miss one single day! Of course, there have been times where I complained about noisy people right under my window outside at night or about my favourite bar being fully-packed, but everytime I'm walking down the streets in my beloved neighborhood with its interesting-looking people coming from all over the world and the huge selection of bars and restaurants, I'm glad to be part of it! It's so relaxing to know that you get everything you want 24/7 and that you can easily meet up with friends in the park nearby, although you're not perfectly dressed up because people do not give a F*** here! :)

I came to Berlin four years ago due to my bachelor university program "International Business". I started looking for an own flat because of some unpleasant flat sharing experiences before and I found this sunny top floor flat in the heart of Berlin. Now I alreday finished my bachelor's degree and continued with the master's programm. Besides studying marketing, finance or accounting, I'm pretty easygoing and love spending time with my friends, especially in Friedrichshain , Kreuzberg or Mitte.
Further, I do enjoy swimming, visiting concerts, dancing or chilling in the park.
When you guys arrive, I will personally hand over the keys and will be glad to give you further information on my favorite places in Berlin and all other stuff like public transportation, shopping, museums etc...
Maybe we can also meet up for drinks and you guys can already report about your first impressions of my flat, the neighborhood and your time in Berlin.

Can't wait to get to know you ;)

Best,
André

Hervorzuheben ist dabei das niedrige Preisniveau der Restaurants und Gaststätten in der Umgebung der Wohnung. Hier zahlt man keine "Touristenpreise" in der Pizzeria oder Kneipe!

Ca. 15 Gehminuten entfernt befindet sich die über 300 Hektar große „Tempelhofer Freiheit“ (der ehemalige Zentralflughafen) mit umfangreichen Sportmöglichkeiten wie Inlinern, Surfen, Skateboarden, Joggen und Grillmöglichkeit.

host_about:
Alsacienne dont le cœur bat désormais outre-rhin, je vis l’Europe au quotidien entre la région transfrontalière Strasbourg-Ortenau et Berlin, en espérant peut-être un jour devenir une vraie berlinoise. Mais c'est quoi au juste une berlinoise ?
Entre ici et là-bas, seule, en amoureux ou avec mes enfants, Berlin reste le lieu d'espaces de liberté nouveaux, de découvertes à faire et à refaire, de surprises et d'inspirations nouvelles alimentant mon quotidien et les projets du futur.
Les temps de mes absences, j'ouvre mon précieux chez-moi berlinois à quelques hôtes de confiance pour leur faire partager ce qui dans cette ville me fait vibrer...J'ouvre désormais également mes portes à Kehl sur la rive du Rhin pour faire profiter de manière authentique et simple les voyageurs de passage de la qualité de vie de ma région transfrontalière. Et j'espère bien être là pour vous y accueillir en personne !

name: Light, central & quiet flat
description:
Quiet bedroom in a beautifully light and spacious flat in a residential part of the centre of Berlin, Berlin Mitte. 

Convenient location for touristic sights, bars and restaurants; only a few minutes walk from the underground station and close to restaurant mile Torstraße.
neighborhood_overview:
The neighbourhood is residential and calm, and only a short walk from popular bars, cafes and restaurants. 

Opposite the flat is a small park with a playground, a Sunday flea market and an organic food market on Fridays. 

There are several grocery shopping options around: A large supermarket (Kaisers) is 2 minutes walk away, an organic food supermarket is minutes away and a small organic food shop is 1 minute walk away. 

There are several cafes on the Arkonaplatz square and further cafes, bars and restaurants within a 5-minute walking distance.

Within a 5-minute walk you can reach Zionskirchplatz, Oderberger Straße and Kastanienallee, with many more restaurants, cafes and bars; and in 10-15 minutes you reach Torstraße, with some of the most known restaurants in Berlin and a favourite evening location among many Berliners.

description:
Our quiet and sunny 1 room - apartment is located in the heart of Berlin – Schöneberg, directly on Nollendorfplatz. The apartment has a spacious living room – bedroom, a  kitchenette, a bathroom and a balcony, it was newly renovated in 2015. The apartment has a comfortable double bed. Fully equipped kitchen for 2 persons. TV with many cable programs, W-Lan , stereo , storage facilities for luggage and clothing. right outside the front door.
ReNo.: 07/Z/ZA/001488-16
neighborhood_overview: Das Apartment ist zentral gelegen mit unmittelbarer Nähe zum Kudamm, Berlins berühmter Einkaufsstraße und Flaniermeile, viele Lokale und Cafés erwarten Sie in unmittelbarer Nachbarschaft. Zentrale Citylage mit direkter und schneller Erreichbarkeit aller Berliner Ziele in West und Ost. Ein abschließbarer Parkplatz kann kostenfrei genutzt werden. Ein schöne Wohnung für einen schönen Urlaub. Sie wohnen in perfekter Lage zwischen City-West und City-Ost. Optimal gelegen im interessanten Kiez zwischen dem Kurfürstendamm und dem Potsdamer Platz. Zahlreiche Shopping-Möglichkeiten, aber auch lebhaftes Kultur-, Kiez- und Nachtleben liegen in der Nähe. Der schönste Berliner Wochenmarkt am Winterfeldtmarkt ist in unmittelbarer Nähe. ( Markttage sind Mittwoch und Samstag ) Hausregeln Rauchen verboten Keine Partys oder Veranstaltungen Eine Reinigungsgebühr wird berechnet und ist im Endpreis inkludiert.

description: Beautiful, perfectly-located, 90sqm, 2-Bedroom-Apartment with high-ceilings, Flatscreen, fast-wifi, large kitchen. Subway/Tram/Buses are literally right outside the door. Countless bars & small restaurants in this friendly SOHO-like neighbourhood.
neighborhood_overview:

host_about:
Hi there,
my name is Frederic, and I live and work in Berlin. I grew up in Spain and Germany, but have always travelled a lot. I graduated in the US and continued my studies in Italy. I then moved to Switzerland before I came to Berlin in 2012. 

I have had amazing guests from many different countries in the world. Whenever I'm renting out my flat I try to get out of the city to explore a new one. 

I'm looking forward to hearing your story and welcoming you in my home.

name: 11D Landmark /Checkpoint Charlie/121m2/2BATH/3BR
description:
The Downtown Landmark near Checkpoint Charlie.
A HOLIDAY HOME IN A NEW over 120 YEARS OLD CENTRAL MONUMENT !
The only place that 100 percent survived the 2nd world war in this central area, with a preserved history.
BEST LOCATION (city center near Checkpoint Charlie, most famous sights can be reached by foot), MOST BEAUTIFUL HOUSE OF THE AREA in the legendary street Friedrichstrasse, TOP CONDITION, QUIET (no drive through, pedestrian zone starts 200 meters away).
neighborhood_overview:
THE BEST CENTRAL LOCATION BECAUSE:

most sights are within walking distance: 2 minutes to Checkpoint Charlie (the most famous symbol of the Cold War); Jewish Museum (the most significant example of contemporary architecture) is our immediate neighbor; 15 minutes to Martin Gropius Bau (main showroom); 20 minutes to Potsdamer Platz (most popular attraction of the New Berlin); 15 minutes to the Gendarmenmarkt (one of the most beautiful marketplaces); 30 minutes to the Brandenburg Gate (the symbol of reunification) and the Reichstag (most famous landmark); 30 minutes to the Museum Island (UNESCO World Heritage Site) with: Old Museum, New Museum, Old National Gallery, Bodemuseum and Pergamon Museum. At Hallesches Tor (3 minutes) is the dock for Berlin's most popular boat tour: the bridge tour.

Art, beauty, multicultural

Is the new center of the Berlin art galleries at this point. Here is the line between alternative and multicultural district of Kreuzberg and
host_about: Trained as a filmmaker (NFTS). Lived, studied and worked in Bucharest (Romania), Berlin, London, Lodz (Poland) and Kishinev (Moldova). name: Cozy Apartment in Heart of Berlin
description:
My cozy appartment is at the 4th floor facing the courtyard: that's way there is so much light and it's so quite.
Lovely neighbourood very well connected with Alexanderplatz: from here you can go everywhere! 10 minutes walk from trendy Mitte.
neighborhood_overview:
My lovely neighbourood, the Winzkiez, is the quintessence of Berlin: 15 minutes walk from Berlin's most representative symbol, the Television Tower in Alexanderplatz, but far away from the crowded tourists.routes, 10 minutes walk from the trendy and lively bars on the Torstrasse and Rosenthalerplatz, but very quite and safe. 
The Museum Insel, with it's Pergamon Museum, the Altes Museum (with the stunning egiptian collection and the Nefertiti) are just two bus stops from Alexanderplatz.
A 7to24 supermarket is just 5 minutes walk, there are a bio supermarket and many nice cafes where you can enjoy a lovely brunch before starting to explore the city!
On Saturdays you can go to thre lovely local products' market in Kollwitzplatz: you can shop fresh fruit and vegetable, and also enjoy a meal or a drink at the market: stawberries prosecco is my favourite ;-)
host_about:
Hallo! I'm Sonia, i live in Berlin since 2009 but i moved a lot before coming here!
Travelling is for me a life-style, so from time to time i rent my home and leave for a while: i love to explore new cities,go to museum and festivals, or just fly south and lie down in the sun. 
Family and nature is what makes me feel at home - thats why my little cozy Berlin appartment is furnished with vintage family pieces and a lot of wood and natural materials.

Friedrichshain is famous for its nightlife, its bars and restaurants. Right around the corner you find the famous Frankfurter Allee - the former Stalinallee - a historic housing project of the East Germany - correctly German Democratic Republic, now also a good place to see a lovely sunset, if you look to Alexanderplatz direction!      
The apartment is in house number 6 - in number 2 is a bakery - opposite the house number 6 a very good ice-shop. Special highlights are the former central airport Tempelhof, the Liquidrom in Möckernstr 10, Akazienstr, Golzstr

Winterfeldplatz Wed + Sat 8 am to 4:00 pm.
Rathaus Schöneberg Tue + Fri 8 am to 1 pm
Crellestraße Wed + Sat 10 am to 3 pm
host_about:
Mit viel Liebe fürs Detail und viel Sachverstand für historische Objekte haben die namhaften Berliner Architekten Peter Hapke und Andreas Zerr die besondere Herausforderung angenommen, die Ferienremise zu einem ganz besonderen Ort zu machen. 

Das Ergebnis ist eine Urlaubs- und Eventlocation, die die ganz besondere Charakteristik eines Altbaus mit modernen Designelementen verbindet und dadurch einen außergewöhnlichen Charme kreiert, der den Besucher in seinen Bann zieht.

Das Architektenduo war nach den Jahren der deutschen  Teilung an vielen Projekten beim Entstehen des neuen Berlin beteiligt.

Gestaltung und verantwortliche Planung und Leitung wichtiger Bauwerke:
- Sanierung Schillertheater für Daniel Barenboim und die Deutsche Staatsoper
- Aussichtsturm Dokumentation Berliner Mauer in der Bernauer Straße
- Errichtung des Denkmals Bücherverbrennung nach den künstlerischen Ideen des   Bildhauers Micha Ullmann
- Sanierung und Umbauten an der Komischen Oper Berlin
- Sanierung und Umbauten am Kinder und Jugendtheater an der Parkaue
- Verantwortliche Leitung bei der Errichtung vieler Kunstwerke in Berlin
- Wettbewerbserfolge: Kunst am Bau Olympiastadion, Volksoper in Wien und   Dokumentationszentrum in Ramstein

You can get to the heart of Prenzlauer Berg in 6 minutes and to Alexander Platz (the centre of Berlin) in 12 minutes – door-to-door. Unweit des angesagten Bergmannkiezes mit Restaurants und zahlreichen Einkaufsmöglichkeiten. Das ehemalige Flughafenfeld Tempelhof ist ebenfalls fußnah.
 Ein  lebens- und liebenswerter Ort zum Wohnen. Das autofreie Gelände ist eine Oase mitten in der Großstadt – ein Musterbeispiel innerstädtischer Bebauung.
 Im Viktoria Quartier profitieren Sie  von einer Lage direkt an dem vor über 120 Jahren angelegten Viktoriapark. Die Verkehrsanbindung ist optimal,  es sind lediglich wenige Gehminuten zum öffentlichen Nahverkehr.

Experience a charming and undoubtedly unique stay in an object located on the site of the historic brewery in Kreuzberg. This quite hip location is very close to the exciting Bergmann Kiez area and not far from restaurants, shops and more. Access to the former Tempelho

name: Centre Quiet 2 Room Flat WiFi, Anmeldung
description: A very quiet apartment in the historical centre of Berlin, ca. 8 min. walk to the Main Railway Station (Hauptbahnhof). Several main museums in a walking distance. One bedroom, 50m²,old building.Huge garden. Excellent transportation! No stairsclimbing
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in historical part of the very centre of the old city. The 3 stories buildings around the area were originally designed for the army veterans of the French-Prussian war, mostly for those, who couldn't afford to pay the rent to stay in the city. Later the area was populated with the doctors, nurses and students of the Charité, the medical faculty of the Humboldt University of Berlin. 

Most of the most important museums (Museum Island, Brandenburger Gate, Hamburger Bahnhof, Reichstag) are located within 5 to 30 min. walking. 

In 70 meters distance from the house it used to be the boarder between East and West Berlin.

In case of medical emergency - 24h/7d ER of the University Clinic Charité is in 5 minute walk.
host_about:
I work as a medical doctor and this is the summer apartment, that we rent sometimes. According to the new rules of the government of Berlin, being inforced from the 1th May 2016, we cannot rent the flat for the period of time less than 220 days. In the past we were accepting stays of at least 7 days, so we collected a lot of references, that you are more than welcome to read.
Our intention in the moment are the longer term contracts.

name: Hidden Gem in Charlottenburg
description: Welcome! I have a bright, spacious guestroom for rent in my charming flat, in a central, green, and quiet Berlin Kiez, full of flair and history. We'll share my fully equipped kitchen for coffee, talks, and  light meals, as well as the small bathroom. Non-smokers only, women preferred. The room is perfect for experienced travelers, researchers, or conference attendees, a peaceful home from home after a busy day of meetings or city explorations.
neighborhood_overview:
What I love about my neighborhood? Everything!!! 
With the hype of some Eastern neighborhoods fading people flock back to where life has always been cosmopolitan and urban at its best - in the City West. Charlottenburg is one of the neighborhoods least affected by the fall of the Berlin wall, simply keeping its charm and elegance. Dubbed the New West when it was built in the early 20th century, ever since it has been a culturally rich, tranquil, green yet central area. In the Golden 20s, this was Berlin's trendiest neighborhood and attracted actors, artists, writers alike. Today you're surrounded by tons of restaurants, movie theaters, galleries, bars, parks, boutiques, farmers' markets, shopping malls from high-end to convenience store and two of the cities best jazz clubs are nearby. Streets are tree-lined and keep the beautiful modernist gas lamps for which Berlin is also famous...
host_about: Hello, I love hosting guests and meeting new people from everywhere! Some envy me for my travel job - doing international research and innovation scouting for smart  solutions in health care. I lived and worked in many countries, with many favorites. I'm in love with San Francisco and the Bay Area - wonderful people, great weather, best restaurants ever, but Italy, Spain, or London are only a two hour flight away from Berlin - always tempting!

name: Cosy Sleep inn ~ Great area ✨
description:
My place is perfect for short stays and allows full privacy:

- Large, calm and comfortable room in a typical Berliner "Altbau" (ancient construction)
- Pretty neighborhood of Schöneberg, peaceful but very animated: restaurants, cafés, bars, supermarkets in walking distance 
- Many bus and metro stations: 4 subway stops away from Potsdamerplatz and Brandenburg Gate 
- Clean and clear bathroom, fresh sheets, towels and soaps
- Lots of informations in the room about Berlin and the neighborhood
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is amazing! I fell in love with it first time I saw it. 
First, it is not too far from the Center: in my good days it takes me 15 minutes by bike to go to Potsdamer Platz. It is only 4 S-Bahn Stations away!
The  street is very quiet and crowned by the extraordinary Gasometer (I love this Gasometer more than the Eiffel Tower!;) There's almost no cars passing by and still the neighborhood is unbelievably alive and animated a few minutes away;
There are many green spaces around and trees everywhere, it smells so good in the summer! 
Everything is 2 steps away: subway and bus stops, shops, restaurants, bars and cafes, many Art galleries, outdoors markets... 
For me (I experience it every day) Schöneberg is one of the best neighborhood of Berlin. Beautiful, charming, full of life and tolerant people... Here lived Marlene Dietrich and David Bowie and was born Albert Einstein ;) Here, John Fitzgerald Kennedy once said: "I am a Berliner!".
host_about:
I'm french and come from the suburb of Paris. After a few visits in Berlin something in me fell for this town... I decided to move here. I like to leave aboard, I spent a few years in America when I was younger, most of the time in New-Orleans. 
Other things I like... staying up late when everybody's sleeping, sing and play guitar, read with my cat while drinking tee... 
Wine with friends, good food and spiritual conversations....

I take pleasure preparing the room for a new traveller, make him comfortable and welcome. It's always a surprise to discover a new personality especially that you people come from all over the world!
As an Hostess I'm never the same, I guess cause I adapt myself to you: If you want privacy that's fine with me, if you need some help or a little chat I'm here for you too!

Liebe Grüße und bis bald!

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in North Neukölln or as the natives call it, 'Kreuz-Kölln' because we border Kreuzberg. For that reason I usually prefer to rent it out to one party during for the whole period, (so I don´t have to organize transitions in my absence). But of course it is also possible.
neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is strange even though this is changing now. This used to be a run down industrial area with lots of factory ruins around. you can walk down to the river in 2 minutes. Although very central it was a no mans land, because in this area used to be the border between East and West.  Now it is an example of gentrification versus squat culture. At this point you can still see both. Since I have moved in here residential and commercial buildings have been mushrooming all around my place. At the same time there is still Tipiland, an alternative tent settlement at the river, the Köpi, one of the oldest still existing squats a few meters down the road and a couple blocks south you are in the heart of northern Kreuzberg (SO 36) but there is also a park nearby with a pond where I skate when the ice is frozen (Engelbecken). As the place is situated on the edge between Friedrichshain, Mitte and Kreuzberg no neighbourhood (including prenzlauer berg or neukölln) is really far away. A

description: New apartment in trendy quarter Prenzlauer Berg has a distinctive Bauhaus architecture style dating back to 1930 with beautiful backyard.12 min by tram to centre of Berlin  (Hackescher Markt).
neighborhood_overview:
Prenzlauer Berg is characterised by old buildings, the majority of which come from the turn of the 20th century (1889 to 1905). Over 80% of all housing in this area was constructed before 1948, with the oldest building still standing being from 1848 at 77 Kastanienallee. In the second World War, relatively few buildings were destroyed in comparison to other areas of the city. The area was neglected in the time of the German Democratic Republic, and the last ruins were cleared away only at the beginning of the 1970s. After the fall of the Berlin Wall and subsequent German Reunification, the dilapidated structures in many areas were rehabilitated, and since the middle of the 1980s empty lots have been closed up.

neighborhood_overview: About my neighborhood there is little to say because it has a lot to offer: there are a lot of bars, coffee places, restaurants in every kinda style. There are also restaurants mentioned in the Lonely Planet around here even though I bet you will find better places when you stay here! every here and there between the gastronomic highlights there are little unique shops where people just realize there dream but also some start ups of the creative scene. What you can still see here is the changing city: the walls tell and sometimes even scream their history at you while  right next to it there is a vegan burger place. You still see a lot of real "Berliners" mixed in the new urban hipster multicultural city scene. When you take a couple of stations by the metro or the bike you will be at Charly´s Checkpoint really fast and by looking at the naive pavement and the couple of wall rests you can only imagine what it means for a city to have been divided by the former two big super powers. <br

name: Your Perfect place in the City.
description: This cosy one bedroom apartment is fully equipped with everything you could need for your stay in Berlin. 2 stops from Alexanderplatz, amazing connections to get all around the city. Everything you need at your door with a grocery store and bakery right outside!
neighborhood_overview: Great location! There are 3 supermarkets, a bakery, bank and some cute cafes right around the corner. You are a stone throw away from the very trendy Oranienstrasse, the cultural heart of Kreuzberg. Its a very friendly and safe neighbourhood with amazing connections for public transport.
host_about:
Irish girl living in Berlin.
I am an Aerial Artist (yes, like in Cirque du Soleil). I am really often traveling because of my job and I also use airbnb quite a bit. I know how it is to be away from home and that is why I use Airbnb every time and not a hotel because I like my comforts - like a couch to sit on, and space, a supermarket and a view! I love Berlin and I am super happy to recommend you places to go, things to see or just help in general with anything you may need.

Also in walking distance you find the famous pioneer and event areas of the former Tempelhof Airport.

name: In the heart of Prenzlauer Berg
description: Renovated apartment – ideal for families with young children or for a group of friends wanting to enjoy one of the best neighbourhoods in Berlin.
neighborhood_overview:
The flat is in the great neighborhood of Prenzlauer Berg, the best-preserved pre-WWI part of Berlin. Our tree-lined, cobbled street leads onto Helmholzplatz, a wonderful green square surrounded by cool bars, cafes, restaurants, and boutique shops. It is perfect for families – it has a great playground and a large old-fashioned toy store  that kids adore – or for young people wanting to chill out in the many small cafes or on the green spaces. 

The other great square in the neighbourhood, Kollwitzplatz, is a 10 minute walk. It has a great farmers market twice a week where you can get a delicious take-away or fresh ingredients for a home cooked meal. The Kulturbrauerei with its clubs, bars and cinemas is 2 minutes away. Also close by is the Mauer Park, the biggest flea market in Berlin with loads of live acts. 

All the shops you may need – organic grocery stores, supermarkets, deli shops and farmer’s markets are either on our street or nearby. 

You will a
host_about:
I am German and during my studies in Berlin I lived in Prenzlauer Berg. This is also the place where I met my future wife Miriam, so we both have a strong connection to this place. After university we went to Geneva, where I now work at CERN building  particle accelerators. 

Miriam and I love Berlin so two years ago we saw the opportunity of buying this wonderful flat and jumped at it. We have spent the last two years renovating the place, carefully choosing every detail and piece of furniture to make it our home in Berlin. Whenever we get the chance we spend time in the flat to simply enjoy this great neighborhood. 

We won’t be able to welcome you when you get to the flat but our very good friend from our student days, Ingrid, will be there to help out with whatever is needed.

The local neighbourhood is a renowned nightlife and cultural quarter with numerous recreational offerings, including cafés, bars, clubs, cinemas, galleries, and many more.  There are also supermarkets and green spaces nearby.

neighborhood_overview: The Mitte district is one of the most versatile and most popular area in town. This is where various cultural facilities and entertainment offers are interwoven. The apartment, situated in a quiet side street with an excellent connection to main roads, is located in a charming area. Not only is the apartment bright on sunny days, but the location is also a hub for a number of leisure offers. Have breakfast as in Paris, eat ice-cream as in Mailand or just enjoy a wonderful dinner, all of that you can find in close proximity. Within walking distance you'll find restaurants (Italian, Indian Mexican, plain cooking...), bars, galleries and cafés. And everything else is a few minutes away by public transport.

description:
Being at home in Berlin:  Home sharing* & part time living*.
* ! From 22. Aug- 08.Sept 24 the apartment will be exclusively at guests disposal !

The room is part of a private 2 bedroom apartment,  lying on the 3rd floor (no lift!) of an old typical Berlin 'Gründerzeit' apartment building.

> Reservation
max. 2 Personen
min. 4  nights - max. 14 nights *

Close by the Canal 
Have a walk along its shore and enjoy its surrounding.

Markets: 
> Turkish Market -
every Tuesday and Friday

> Markthalle 9 
Streetfood evening on Thursday 

10 min by subway to city center east, 15 min by subway to city center west.

> Jewish Museum

Outdoor and Indoor Swimming Pools

> Bade Schiff 

... and a lot more, if you feel like.

 I am looking forward to your visit!

neighborhood_overview:

So it is easily reachable to all three., besides to the city center in 13 mins. Friedrichshain has some interesting attractions: there is the EAST SIDE GALERY, the OBERBAUMBRÜCKE and BOXHAGENER PLATZ flea market every Sunday. 

You also have O2 World or even the Velodrom nearby for sporting events or concerts

It is just in front of the beautifully wild Prenzlauer Berg Park from where you can see the whole of Berlin at its top. And a walking distance form Friedrichshain VolksPark for the berliner sun bathing, picnics or BBQs.
