name: Apartment Berlin-Mahlsdorf, 1-[2] Personen
description:
A comfortable apartment in the wonderfully green district of Berlin-Mahlsdorf!

The 20 m² apartment is located at ground level following our holiday home in a quiet green settlement on the eastern outskirts of Berlin.
neighborhood_overview:
Berlin-Marzahn ist ein Teil des Stadtbezirkes Hellersdorf-Marzahn. Bekannt ist der Ort durch seine Plattenbausiedlungen, weniger bekannt durch sein historisches Dorf die alte Dorfkirche und die grünen Anlagen zwischen den Plattenbauten und durch seine Einfamilienhaussiedlungen.
Ein wichtiges Ausflugsziel sind die Gärten der Welt im Erholungspark Marzahn

Sehenswürdigkeiten in der Umgebung des Ferienhauses:

- Gärten der Welt mit thematischen Länderkulturen
- Schloss und Schlosspark Biesdorf
- Wuhletalwanderweg
- Alt-Köpenick mit dem Kunstgewerbemuseum im Schloß
- Gründerzeitmuseum in Mahlsdorf mit Zillekneipe
host_about:
Wir freuen uns darauf Sie ganz herzlichst in unserer wunderschönen Ferienunterkunft begrüßen zu dürfen.

Die Einrichtung der Ferienwohnung erfolgte mit Möbeln im kolonialen Stil. Bei uns finden Sie mit Schnitzereien verzierte Massivholzmöbel, die noch nach überlieferter Handwerkstradition gefertigt wurden, und handbemalte Möbel aus kleinen Handwerksbetrieben aus der Region Rajasthan in Indien.

name: Bright, Central One-Bedroom
description: Centrally-located along the U5 and a grand boulevard in former East Berlin, this light-filled one-bedroom is the heart-filled home of a local artist.
neighborhood_overview:
Karl-Marx-Allee is a monumental boulevard built by the GDR between 1952 and 1960 and begins at Strausberger Platz at the border of Mitte and Friedrichshain in central Berlin. It has been called "Europe's last great street," and East Berlin is exemplified by the impressive apartment structures that run along either side, reaching eight stories high in a Soviet wedding-cake style. You'll find a walking tour marked with plaques along the almost 2 km length, providing details about the historical and architectural significance of the area.

Café Sibylle, one of the first to open along the boulevard, is an 8-minute walk east and still serves homemade cakes and coffee. 5 minutes further brings you to Briefmarken Weine, a small but well-stocked Italian wine bar with great ambiance. In the direction of Alexanderplatz, you'll find Kino International close-by, an impressive, historical film theater that regularly hosts premieres. All along the boulevard, you'll find renowned art galler
host_about: I'm a musician, teacher, and designer, originally from California, living in Europe since 2010. In 2014, I bought and renovated my first home, a one-bedroom apartment in central Berlin that I rent out when traveling. I am continuing a strong family tradition of hosting by offering my home here. We acted as a host family for many foreign exchange students over the years and welcomed many friends, friends-of-friends, and of course family, as well — and friends who've become family! I take pride in offering a special space, my home, not a soulless four walls, and I of course take special care as a guest, as well. When traveling, I get to the ocean or sea whenever possible and particularly love to visit anywhere I have a connection, however tenuous. You never know where you'll find new friend-family!

name: Welcome Home, welcome to Kant Strasse 63
description: Our spacious, warm, fully-equipped, and extremely well-connected central Berlin apartment offers an oasis of calm and period charm in this exciting and vibrant city. Its back courtyard location guarantees a good nights sleep in either the spacious master bedroom or our other bedroom with two single  beds. The living room sofa can also be pulled out if you need it, and there is a baby bed. Free Wifi, large kitchen and bathroom, washer / drier, and lovely living / dining room. You will love it.
neighborhood_overview: One of the most elegant districts in Berlin, Charlottenburg exudes old-world glamour. Named after Queen Charlotte of Prussia, it is stuffed with French-influenced architecture, stylish and ethnic / street food restaurants and cafes to suit all tastes and budgets, shopping streets, theatres, museums and peaceful parks. The area has always attracted Berliners and tourists, from celebrities, artists, and politicians who haunt the famous Paris Bar, to today's young families who have made the area their home. The iconic Kurfürstendamm - the Champs-Elysées of Berlin - runs parallel to Kant Strasse, and there is Charlottenburg Palace, the Kaiser Wilhelm Memorial church, Schiller theatre, Deutsche Opera, the list goes on and on.
host_about: Hi, we love Berlin. Although we currently live in Switzerland there is  part of us that is always in Berlin. There is so much history, and so much that is contemporary too. description: Live right in the center the action - in the middle of hip Friedrichshain. In a newly renovated, cozy and comfortable design-apartment. This cozy nest is right in one of the most vibing places in Berlin. 
There are lots of restaurants and bars right on your doorstep e.g. Simon-Dach-Strasse & Boxhagener Platz - some of literally the best bars in Berlin are just next door! World renowned clubs like Berghain and Watergate are within 10min walking distance!! Same walking distance to many other clubs and bars near Warschauerstrasse (Suicide Circus, Chalet and, a little further, all of Kreuzberg).
There is great Brunches right next door on Sundays, and many restaurants and very good fast food places otherwise.
It's 4 subway stations from Alexanderplatz; 10 min walk to the Berlin wall and the Spree river full of beachbars.
There is a super Market IN the house, you can literally get your shopping done in your pyjamas! There is also a big Kaisers supermarket within walking distance which is open 24h and 2 Bio Supermarketes even closer! Every Saturday there is a big lovely farmers Market on Boxhagener Platz (
